Nigeria’s Kaduna State Plan Shares Sale to Investors, Trust Says

-- B y   E l i s h a   B a l a - G b o g b o
-- 
2011-03-07T08:35:53Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-07/nigeria-s-kaduna-state-plan-shares-sale-to-investors-trust-says.html
  Nigeria ’s north-central Kaduna State
plans to sell 70 percent of its shares in three companies,  Daily
Trust  reported, citing state Governor Ibrahim Yakowa.  The companies involved are Zaria Pharmaceutical, Ikara Food
Processing and Kachia Ginger Processing, the Abuja-based
newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Elisha Bala-Gbogbo in Abuja at 
 ebalagbogbo@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dulue Mbachu at 
 dmbachu@bloomberg.net . 